The paper discusses the development of a framework for introspective behavior in perception systems, specifically in the context of vision-based autonomous MAV flight in outdoor natural environments. This involves the use of machine learning techniques to predict failures in the system directly from input sensor data. Given the focus on robotics and computer vision, as well as the use of machine learning, the most likely sub-category is cs.RO (Robotics and Control). However, the paper also involves computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and machine learning (cs.LG), as well as systems and control (cs.SY).
